@startuml settings_propagation
!include dark-theme.puml
' Revised 2026-05-13: applied audit_23/Wave-1-fix amendments
title Settings change propagation - who reacts to AppSettings.Changed

actor User
participant "Page.xaml.cs\n(General/Flyout/TrayIcon/Monitors/\nHotkeys/Environmental/Theme)" as PG
participant "AppSettings\n(model + event)" as AS
participant "AppSettings.Save\n(XML on disk)" as ASD
participant "App.OnSettingsChanged\n(central funnel)" as AOC
participant "MonitorService\n.OnSettingsChanged" as MS
participant "NightLightProvider\n.OnSettingsChanged" as NLP
participant "BrightnessFlyout\n.OnAppSettingsChanged" as BF
participant "EnvironmentalCurveService" as ECS
participant "SettingsWindow\n.OnAppSettingsChanged" as SW
participant "TAWPFColorPicker\n.OnAppSettingsChanged" as CP
participant "TrayIconManager" as TIM
participant "GlobalHotkeyService" as GHS
participant "PDBSymbolResolver" as PDB
participant "UpdateCheckService\n(GitHub poller; cf410f7)" as UCS

== Edit on a settings page ==

User -> PG : edit any setting
PG -> AS  : property setter
PG -> ASD : _settings.Save()  (synchronous XML write)
PG -> AS  : _settings.RaiseChanged()
note right of PG $TINT_NEUTRAL
  Pages call SaveAndNotify():
  Save() then RaiseChanged().
  ThemePage.ColorChanged
  bypasses RaiseChanged - the
  NullableThemeColor multicast
  already raises Changed via
  AppSettings.WireColorCallbacks.
end note

== Multicast to subscribers ==

AS -> AOC : Changed
AS -> MS  : Changed
AS -> NLP : Changed
AS -> BF  : Changed
AS -> SW  : Changed (when open)
AS -> CP  : Changed (when picker open)

== App.OnSettingsChanged - central funnel ==

AOC -> AOC : UpdateThemeResources(effective)\n  (rebuilds Theme*/Environmental* brushes,\n   CornerRadius*, SliderThumbGlyph*)
AOC -> TIM : IsLightTheme, IconStyle,\nUpdateCooldownMs (= BrightnessUpdateRateMs),\nIsScrollEnabled, ApplyTrayIconColors\n  -> RequestTrayRefresh()
AOC -> MS  : WriteCooldownMs (= BrightnessUpdateRateMs)\nValidationDwellMs
AOC -> PDB : ApplyPDBDownloadTimeout\n  (NightLightPDBDownloadTimeoutSeconds)
AOC -> GHS : Apply(_appSettings.Hotkeys)\n  (re-register WM_HOTKEY bindings)
AOC -> AOC : _contextMenu = CreateContextMenu()\n  (rebuild tray right-click menu)
AOC -> BF  : _activeFlyout.NotifyUpdateStateChanged()\n  (pull live ShowUpdateNotificationsEnabled +\n   CheckForUpdatesEnabled)

== MonitorService side reactions ==

MS -> MS : _display.OperationTimeoutMs\n  = DDCOperationTimeoutMs
alt MonitorIdentityStrategy changed
    MS -> MS : Refresh()  (re-key every MonitorInfo)
else strategy unchanged
    MS -> MS : ApplyNameOverridesToExisting()\nResortMonitors()
end

== NightLightProvider side reactions ==

alt NightLightFallbackMode changed
    NLP -> NLP : InvalidateBackendCache()\nGetCachedBackend()  (re-probe Registry vs SettingsHandler)
else mode unchanged
    NLP -> NLP : skip (only fallback mode matters)
end

== BrightnessFlyout side reactions ==

BF -> BF : UpdateMasterFromEnabledIndividuals()\n  (DynamicIconBrightnessTracking, MasterSliderMode)
BF -> NLP : GetStrength() / IsEnabled() readback\n  -> sync NightLightMonitor.Brightness\n  (handles InvertNightLightSlider flip)
BF -> BF : Redock() if AllowFlyoutUndock turned off
BF -> BF : raise PropertyChanged for\nShowFlyout*, AllowFlyoutUndock,\nShowMaster/IndividualSliders,\nShowNightLightKelvinLabel,\nInvertNightLightSlider,\nIsCurveAbsoluteMode, ...
BF -> ECS : _curveService.Start() + Evaluate()\n  (pull EnvironmentalCurveTickIntervalMs,\n   EnvironmentalOffsetMode, smoothness, location)

== UpdateCheckService side reactions ==

AS  -> UCS : Changed
UCS -> UCS : if AutoCheckForUpdates flipped\n  -> Start / Stop loop;\n  if UpdateCheckIntervalMinutes changed\n  -> Restart (cancel current Delay);\n  if UpdateChannel changed\n  -> next poll uses new feed

== SettingsWindow / color picker chrome ==

SW -> SW : ApplyOuterCornerRadius\n  (EnableRoundedCorners)
CP -> CP : ApplyOuterCornerRadius\nUpdateChannelSliderThumbs

== Out-of-band saves (no RaiseChanged) ==

note over NLP $TINT_AMBER
  NightLightProvider.SetStrength
  may persist NightLightLastNonZeroStrength
  by calling AppSettings.Save() directly -
  no RaiseChanged, so subscribers don't fan
  out for what is effectively a sticky cache
  field used only by the next toggle-on.
end note

note over AS $TINT_BLUE
  Save() runs on every page edit (Page.SaveAndNotify
  calls Save first, then RaiseChanged).
  Heavy lists (KnownDisplays, MonitorOrder) still ride
  on AppSettings, so a MonitorService.Refresh that
  rewrites them costs one XML write.

  AppSettings.Save now uses atomic temp+rename
  (M-04 fix). IOExceptions are logged rather than
  swallowed silently.
end note

note over ECS $TINT_AMBER
  ECS does NOT subscribe to AppSettings.Changed.
  Setting edits made during a closed-flyout window
  (e.g. EnvironmentalCurveTickIntervalMs, smoothness,
  lat/lon) won't take effect on the curve service
  until the flyout reopens and OnAppSettingsChanged
  there pulls the live values into the service via
  Start() + Evaluate().

  ECS DOES subscribe to SystemEvents.TimeChanged
  for DST / clock changes - those reset the curve's
  date-keyed cache (_cachedShifted*) so the next
  Evaluate observes the new wall-clock anchor.
end note

note over BF $TINT_AMBER
  BrightnessFlyout.OnAppSettingsChanged does NOT
  re-read the curve enable flags from AppSettings.
  The flyout setter is the canonical writer (steps
  1..9 sync on UI dispatcher). Any out-of-band
  AppSettings writer (none today) would not
  propagate to the service / flyout mirrors.
end note

note over AOC $TINT_RESOLVED
  Hotkey edits take effect immediately:
  AOC calls GHS.Apply on every settings
  change, so users don't need a hotplug or
  app restart for new bindings to register.
end note

@enduml
